The paper deals with natural language understanding and reasoning about quantities, which are common topics in computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Unit Dependency Graphs (UDGs) involves machine learning techniques for inducing and leveraging domain knowledge, which are also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of a constrained inference framework, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV).
